PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

DATA: Budget Categories
MARKER: budget_categories
INTENT: holds all budget categories and their balances
---
The app holds a list of budget categories. Each category has a name, a current balance, and a monthly limit.

STRUCTURE: Home Screen
MARKER: home_screen
INTENT: the main screen showing budget overview
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a summary of total income and expenses, a list of categories with their balances, and a floating add category button in the bottom right.

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user adds a new budget category
---
When the user taps the add category button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and monthly limit. The new category is added to the list and its balance is set to zero.

WHEN: Update Category Balance
MARKER: update_category_balance
INTENT: user updates a category's balance
---
When the user taps the edit icon on a category card, a form appears. The user adjusts the balance and confirms. The category's balance is updated and reflected in the list.

ASSERT: Category Balance Validation
MARKER: category_balance_validation
INTENT: ensure category balance does not exceed limit
---
A category's balance cannot exceed its monthly limit. If the balance is updated to exceed the limit, it is automatically capped at the limit.

SURFACE: Category Card
MARKER: category_card
INTENT: labels and styles for category cards
---
The category card displays the category name, current balance, and monthly limit. The card has an edit icon and a checkbox for marking the category as completed.